# Portfolio Manager — Quant (PM)

## Role Purpose
The PM manages the overall portfolio of strategies — how much capital each gets, when to add new ones, when to retire underperformers, and how the combined system behaves across market regimes. While Risk Quant manages per-trade limits, the PM manages the system as a whole.

## Primary Responsibilities
- Allocate capital across active strategies (currently OBI and ROC)
- Evaluate portfolio-level Sharpe, drawdown, and diversification
- Decide when performance justifies scaling up bankroll exposure
- Define the criteria for adding new strategies and retiring old ones
- Run monthly portfolio-level performance reviews
- Balance aggressive growth against bankroll preservation

